         AddConsequenceRealization, the three accessor methods, and Equals are kept VERBATIM. Same
         auto-pickup as patched/Structure.cs/Inventory.cs above, no explicit Compile Include. -->
    <!-- Task Phase4T4: patched/ConsequenceExtensions.cs keeps ONLY the AggregatedConsequencesBinned
         FilterByCategories overload; the sibling AggregatedConsequencesByQuantile overload is a
         genuine compile blocker (that type isn't compiled into this project). patched/
         StudyAreaConsequencesBinned.cs drops WriteToXML/ReadFromXML (calls AggregatedConsequencesBinned
         methods the Task 3 patch already dropped) and ConvertToStudyAreaConsequencesByQuantile
         (references the uncompiled quantile-result types); GetAggregateEmpiricalDistribution,
         SampleMeanDamage, and ConsequenceExceededWithProbabilityQ are dropped too, matching the C++
         port's scope (not hard compile blockers, but out of scope; see that file's header).
         Everything else (both ctors, AddNewConsequenceResultObject,
         AddExistingConsequenceResultObject, both AddConsequenceRealization overloads,
         PutDataIntoHistograms, Equals, GetSpecificHistogram, RemainingIterations,
         ResultsAreConverged, ToUncertainPairedData, GetAssetCategories/GetDamageCategories,
         GetConsequenceResult) is kept VERBATIM. Same auto-pickup as the patched/ files above, no
         explicit Compile Include. -->
    <!-- Task Phase4T5: patched/HydraulicDataset.cs keeps ONLY the two pure-numeric
         CorrectDryStructureWSEs overloads (VERBATIM) plus a thin CorrectAllProfiles wrapper
         reproducing GetHydraulicDatasetInFloatsWithProbabilities's post-read correction loop
